TextChange:
Does "stuff" really bring us happiness, or is it really just filling a hole where we want happiness? I will try and figure out here what I think about materialism and the way we consume in this day and age.
   I am one who really isn't very pacified just by having the newest iphone or the faciest car on the street. Yes, it's always great to get something new and shiny, and for my friends to give me compliments on my newest purchase but inside myself I am never any happier when I spend a bunch of money on something that I really didn't need in the first place. If anything I feel like a fool if I overspend on something just for the "ooh's and ahh's" especially if that something's equivalent could be had for much less with a different brand name on it.
  Think for a minute if you have ever felt down and decided that buying something expensive or blowing a bunch of money on a really expensive trip would make you feel better. Well sure it does, that's why we all do it but does it really change how happy you really are with yourself, no it doesn't. That's something that can only be fixed from within yourself.
  So, the next time you're really down or having a terrible day, maybe try looking inside yourself and seeing what's really causing you to have
